The county government yesterday launched an online platform for the payment of loading zones.Payments will be done through the eJijiPAY system that motorists use to pay for parking.ICT executive Anne Lokidor said payment is completed through simple steps and users will receive an immediate response from the parking office on the progress of requests and payment. &ldquo;This new development will improve the relationship between citizens and the county as it aims at efficient service delivery and transparency in the transport sector,&rdquo; she said.The county launched the electronic payment system &ldquo;eJijipay&rdquo; in June 2014, bringing to an end the manual system, which had many loopholes. Landowners, matatu owners, market vendors, businesspeople already make payments through their phones.